monograph approaches the group of works Frauen based on five areas of analysis, ranging from the production of the figures to the exhibiting of them in diverse contexts. It elucidates at what points, in what manifestations, and with what functions a principle of being kept in a state of flux becomes productive, since this principle is what keeps the large, hundreds-of-kilos-heavy sculptures in motion and thus opens up questions with respect to the human, female figure and options for depicting it in monumental sculpture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aSkulptur. 4aThomas Schütte. 4aWeiblicher Akt.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z97831107507060 cprintz978311067111740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311069319540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110693195423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110693195/original  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK